===Noun===

# an [[odor]] or [[smell]], especially one left by an animal being [[hunt]]ed by [[hound]]s.
# something with a strong [[odor]]. (''the scent of [[flower]]s'' or ''the scent of a [[skunk]]'')
# [[perfume]].
# (''Figurative'') any [[trail]] or trace that can be followed to find something or someone.

====Translations====
*German: [[Duft]] ''m'' (1), [[Duftstoff]] ''m'' (2), [[Parfüm]] ''n'' (3), [[Fährte]] ''f'' (4)

===Transitive verb===

# to detect the scent of.  (''The hounds scented the fox in the woods.'')
# to impart an oder to.  (''Scent the air with burning sage before you begin your meditation.'')

====Translations====
*German: [[wittern]] (1), [[parfümieren]] (2)

